<div class="KonaBody"><p>Reverting your operating system to a previous state without consequences sounds almost like magic. You can quickly return to your work as if nothing happened, even when you don’t know what caused the problem. That’s why the System Restore feature is among the top things ex-Windows users want from Linux.<br />
<span id="more-4536"></span></p>
<p>If you’re one of those users, this guide is for you. You’ll learn the tools that bring System Restore functionality to Linux.</p>
